## Customer [/customers/{id}]

+ Parameters
  + id: `1` (number, required) - The unique ID of the Customer

### GET

Fetch a customer by id.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
                "status": "ok",
                "customer": {
                        "id": 1,
                        "first_name": "...",
                        "last_name": "...",
                        "email": "...",
                        "status": "..."
                }
        }

+ Response 404 (application/json)

        {
                "status": "error",
                "message": "Record Not Found"
        }


### PUT

Edit an existing Customer.

+ Request (body)

        Customer

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
                "status": "ok",
                "customer": {
                        "id": 1,
                        "first_name": "...",
                        "last_name": "...",
                        "email": "...",
                        "status": "..."
                }
        }



# Data Structures

## Customer (object)

- id: `1` (number, required) - The unique ID of the customer.
- first_name: `George` (string, required) - Customer's first name.
- last_name: `Harris` (string, required) - Customer's last name.
- email: `george.harris@takeout.io` (string, required) - Customer's email address.

